    From the manufacturer

    What We Do

    Prepac is a North American designer, manufacturer and drop shipper of functional and stylish RTA (Ready-To-Assemble) Home Furniture.

    Read more

    Prepac Entertainment Furniture

    Altus Floating TV Stands

    The minimalist, off-the floor design of Prepac's Altus Plus Floating TV Stands eliminates the need for a separate wall-mount TV bracket and is the perfect pairing for any flat screen TV up to 60". At 58 inches wide, it includes three compartments for A/V components and a bottom shelf for media with room for 137 Blu-Ray Discs or 93 DVDs. Cables & power bars can be neatly concealed to maintain a clean, modern look. When installed according to the manufacturer’s directions, the Altus Plus has a 165 lbs weight capacity which will accommodate most flat screen TVs and A/V components. Installing the Altus Plus at any height is simple, thanks to its innovative metal hanging rail mounting system. Available in Deep Black, Drifted Gray, Rich Espresso and Pure White laminate finishes.

    Product description

    Color:Black  |  Style Name:Altus Plus Floating TV Stand

    The minimalist, off-the floor design of the Altus plus eliminates the need for a separate wall-mount TV bracket and is the perfect pairing for any flat screen TV up to 60". at 58 inch wide, it boasts three compartments for a/V components and a bottom shelf for media with room for 137 Blu-ray discs or 93 DVDs. Cables & power bars can be neatly concealed to maintain a clean, modern look. When installed according to the manufacturer's directions, the Altus plus has a 165lb weight capacity which will accommodate most flat screen TVs and a/V components. Installing the Altus plus at any height is simple, thanks to its innovative metal hanging rail mounting system. Available in deep black and rich espresso laminate finishes. Proudly manufactured in Canada using carb-compliant, laminated composite wood. Ships ready to assemble with an instruction booklet for easy assembly and links to an installation video. Includes a 5-year manufacturer's limited warranty.

        How does Amazon calculate star ratings?
        Amazon calculates a product’s star ratings based on a machine learned model instead of a raw data average. The model takes into account factors including the age of a rating, whether the ratings are from verified purchasers, and factors that establish reviewer trustworthiness.

        5.0 out of 5 stars It's not a perfect match, but considering it's behind the cable box
        Reviewed in the United States on August 18, 2015
        Color: BlackStyle Name: Altus Plus Floating TV StandVerified Purchase
        If you're looking for an inexpensive floating tv stand, this is it! I only have two MAJOR gripes- First, it's particle board. Secondly, the manufacturer does not include a black backing. I added my own for depth. *see attached images. I purchased a $1 poster board at Walmart. It's not a perfect match, but considering it's behind the cable box, roku and bose receiver, you would never know the difference.

        Build quality 4/5 ...it's particle board, but it's feels sturdy enough. No gripes.
        Ease of construction 5/5 Instructions are clear and precise.
        Ease of installation 3/5. Mounting on the wall was cake (two man job). Wiring install was another story.

        Total time was ~2 hours.
        I would buy this item again for the price ...but would pay triple for something of solid wood.

        Hope this review helps :)

        Lovely Rebel
        5.0 out of 5 stars Definitely worth the money and the effort.
        Reviewed in the United States on September 22, 2016
        Color: BlackStyle Name: Altus Plus Floating TV StandVerified Purchase
        After soliciting help from a few of my male friends with the assembly and mounting of this thing, I found myself sorely on my own.

        After unboxing all of the securely packaged pieces, I felt overwhelmed. I was certain it would be impossible to assemble and mount alone. But I'm pleased to report that all it took was a little concentration and determination. Before I knew it, I'd done it.

        The unit is a little heavy but I was able to haul it up the stairs by myself. Truth be told, the shelf is heaviest when it first arrives in its tall freight like packaging.

        Though not real wood, the quality is still amazing. It's very sturdy, I honestly see it lasting a lifetime if cared for.

        It took me two days and two trips to Lowes to acquire a stud finder and a power drill to finish, but not for level of difficulty. Rather a lack of time. I'd say 4 hours total. The most difficult aspsect of the project was mounting the shelf to the wall. I'd never screwed a bolt into a stud before, it was hard but I did it. Making sure the holes were evenly spaced must be carefully done too for obvious reasons. I used a tape measure because I don't have a ruler, and carefully drew a straight line. I didn't even have to use all four bolts in the bracket, two bolts more than suffice. I applied nearly all of my weight to the shelf after I hung it, and it never even buckled. Hanging the shelf to the bracket was a breeze. I heard a literal click and presto, the mount was complete. To all you ladies out there, I picked up the shelf and hung it to the bracket by myself. If I can do it, so can you.

        My TV is 50 inches, by the way. The shelf is in my bedroom, looks sleek and is definitely a space saver. I love that I can place decorative items on it and whatever else I like. Im thinking of purchasing a second shelf for my extra bedroom and 42 inch tv.

        Go ahead and take the plunge, you won't regret it.

        T
        4.0 out of 5 stars Great product but has a bit of an annoying flaw
        Reviewed in the United States on March 2, 2017
        Color: BlackStyle Name: Altus Plus Floating TV StandVerified Purchase
        This is a great floating TV stand. It is a bit "ikea" style as its composite wood. It looks great but has a bit of a flaw. It is near impossible to get to the underside to plug and unplug electronics if you do as recommended and put a power strip on the underside compartment. There is a about 3x12in area for you to get your hand in to grab the power strip out to figure out and in. if you have any larger power supply type cables, they dont fit while plugged into the power strip, you have to figure out a way to plug them into the power strip while the strip is inside the hole. Its not really possible to plug in everything before putting the stand on the wall either, as it weights a lot, and you have to make sure all your cables are run through the cut outs of each shelf. you will end up getting cables stuck in between the shelf and the wall.

        That said, once you get if figured out, it looks great and works well.

        Though I'm sure a recommendation would go unnoticed by the manufacturer, it would be great if they added a door or latch that gave you access to compartment on the lower section, so you can configure you cables.

        I still recommend, just takes ingenuity to get all the power cabling figured out

        Riley
        5.0 out of 5 stars Works Great
        Reviewed in the United States on December 23, 2013
        Color: BlackStyle Name: Altus Plus Floating TV StandVerified Purchase
        We are extremely happy with this shelf. We'd been looking at wall hanging our components for a while in order to free up some floor space, but nothing we'd found looked like it would do a good job with cable management. Then we found this. Assembly is simple, and once put together, it's very sturdy. Before I wall mounted the TV, I had it sitting on this shelf just like in the advertisement photo.

        What you can't see on any of the pictures from this site, is the large cubby built into the back of this unit. There are cable runs behind each shelf (and between), along with a large open area under the 3 shelves but behind the DVD storage. This area is large enough to easily house a power strip (and one or two power bricks) plus completely cover your outlet and cable jack. The result is a totally clean install, with no visible wires anywhere.

        The entire unit hangs on a black powder-coated steel bracket, so if you ever need to take the shelf down (to paint for example) you just lift it off the wall. While you can do this by yourself, I'd recommend two people as the unit is fairly heavy (around 60lbs) and it would be easy to damage it or the wall if it slipped in your hands while you removed it.

        If you are looking to wall mount your TV and associated components, don't want any visible wires, and are looking for a reasonably easy to way to do it, this shelf will definitely work for you.
